main event: A housewife spotted a stationary orange oval object with a white shadow near it for about 3-5 minutes on April 17, 1966, in Sioux City, Iowa.
interesting points: The observer described the object as being about 30 feet in size., The object appeared orange with a white shadow moving near it., The sighting was made from the observer's kitchen window., There was no sound associated with the object., The conclusion of the report suggested it might have been a star seen through broken cloud cover.
